NAME
	sqlite3_exec - sqlite3 exension: exec statement

SYNOPSIS
	int *sqlite3_exec(string filename, string sql)

DESCRIPTION
	This command is only available if you have the SQLITE3 exension
	available.  Filename is the location of your sqllite database
	and sql is the statment you want to run.

	You can find the exension on github here:
	https://github.com/november-kilo/dgd-lpc-ext

RETURN VALUE
	If extension is not enabled, or filename is unreadable this
	command will return nil.  Otherwise it will return the value
	returned from the external call to sqlite3_exec.

EXAMPLES
        int x;
        string st;

	st = "drop table users";

	x = sqlite3_exec("/tmp/mydatabase.sql", st);
	if (x) {
	   write("Success.\n");
	} else {
	   write("Error in statement: " + st + "\n";
	}

SEE ALSO
